      • setHorizontalMultiplier

        public void setHorizontalMultiplier(int value)
        The horizontal multiplier property will cause the horizontal printing of the object to be scaled by that amount. So a value of two would cause a printing of the object to be double its original width. The default value for this parameter is 1 and the range of valid values is 1 to 2.
        Parameters:
        value - Factor by which to scale the printing horizontally.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - If the parameter values are not in the valid range.
        Since:
        1.0.0

      • setVerticalMultiplier

        public void setVerticalMultiplier(int value)
        The vertical multiplier property will cause the vertical printing of the object to be scaled by that amount. So a value of two would cause a printing of the object to be double its original height. The default value for this parameter is 1 and the range of valid values is 1 to 2.
        Parameters:
        value - Factor by which to scale the printing vertically.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - If the parameter values are not in the valid range.
        Since:
        1.0.0
